<HEAD>Beatles And Hurricanes Poster Goes To Japan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A rare poster advertising the Beatles at Hamburg's
Kaiserkeller was sold for $5,950 to an unidentified Japanese
bidding by telephone, Phillips auctioneers said.
   The poster dates from around 1960, advertising performances by
``original rock 'n' roll Bands'' featuring the Beatles and Rory
Storm and his Hurricanes.
   Beatles drummer Ringo Starr played or the Hurricanes before he
joined the Beatles who, like some other British groups, were famous
in West Germany before they made the big time at home.
   The poster made the top price in Wednesday's sale of 283 lots of
pop and rock music memorabilia which totaled $181,000.
   A Fender Stratocaster cream guitar once owned by Sting, former
lead singer of Police, was bought by Warwick Stone of the Hard Rock
Cafe in Los Angeles for $5,500.
